1. GALE WARNING: NIL SMALL CRAFT WARNING: NIL
2. METEOROLOGICAL SITUATION AT 1500: IRELAND LIES IN A MODERATE TO FRESH
SOUTHERLY AIRFLOW WITH A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE EXTENDING FROM AN ANTICYCLONE
OF 1026 HPA CENTRED TO THE SOUTH. A DEPRESSION OF 959HPA IS CENTRED TO THE
WEST OF ICELAND WITH ITS ASSOCIATED WARM FRONT LYING TO THE EAST OF IRELAND.
AN ASSOCIATED COLD FRONT LIES JUST OFF THE NORTHWEST COAST AND WILL CROSS
THE COUNTRY TONIGHT CLEARING FROM THE SOUTHEAST TOMORROW MORNING.
3. FORECAST FOR IRISH COASTAL WATERS FROM MIZEN HEAD TO ERRIS HEAD TO FAIR
HEAD WIND: NORTHWEST FORCE 3 OR 4 IMMINENT. LATER BACKING WEST TO SOUTHWEST
FORCE 4 OR 5.
WEATHER: CLOUDY WITH RAIN DRIZZLE MIST AND FOG WHICH CLEARING SOUTHEASTWARDS
OVERNIGHT WITH CLOUDY TO FAIR WEATHER FOLLOWING AND JUST A FEW ISOLATED SHOWERS.
VISIBILITY: MODERATE OR POOR IN PRECIPITATION MIST AND FOG. IMPROVING
MOSTLY GOOD OVERNIGHT.
FORECAST FOR IRISH COASTAL WATERS FROM FAIR HEAD TO HOWTH HEAD TO CARNSORE
POINT AND FOR THE IRISH SEA
WIND: SOUTHERLY FORCE 4 OR 5 TOUCHING FORCE 6 AT FIRST IN THE NORTHEAST.
SOON VEERING NORTHWEST FORCE 4 OR 5 NORTH OF WICKLOW HEAD OCCASIONALLY TOUCHING
FORCE 6 IN THE NORTH. VEERING NORTHWEST TO NORTH FORCE 4 OR 5 TOMORROW MORNING.
LATER DECREASING NORTHWEST TO NORTH FORCE 4.
WEATHER: MOSTLY CLOUDY WITH PATCHES OF LIGHT RAIN DRIZZLE AND MIST. MORE
PERSISTENT RAIN AND DRIZZLE WITH MIST AND FOG SOON SPREADING FROM THE NORTHWEST
BUT CLEARING LATER WITH MAINLY FAIR TO CLOUDY WEATHER FOLLOWING.
VISIBILITY: MODERATE OR POOR IN PRECIPITATION MIST AND FOG. LATER IMPROVING
MOSTLY GOOD. FORECAST FOR IRISH COASTAL WATERS FROM CARNSORE POINT TO DUNGARVAN
TO MIZEN HEAD
WIND: SOUTHWEST TO WEST FORCE 3 OR 4. SOON VEERING WEST OR NORTHWEST FORCE
4 OR 5. VEERING NORTHWEST TO NORTH FORCE 4 OR 5 TOMORROW MORNING AND DECREASING
FORCE 2 TO 4 LATER.
WEATHER: CLOUDY AND MISTY WITH PATCHES OF LIGHT RAIN DRIZZLE AND FOG.
MORE PERSISTENT RAIN AND DRIZZLE LATER. IMPROVING CLOUDY TO FAIR BEFORE THE
END OF THE PERIOD.
VISIBILITY: MODERATE OR POOR IN PRECIPITATION MIST AND FOG.
WARNING OF HEAVY SWELL: ON WESTERN SOUTHWESTERN AND NORTHWESTERN COASTS
THIS EVENING AND EARLY TONIGHT.
4. OUTLOOK FOR A FURTHER 24 HOURS UNTIL 1800 TUESDAY 16 NOVEMBER 2021:
WINDS WILL CONTINUE TO BACK SOUTHWESTERLY AND STRENGTHEN ON MONDAY NIGHT
AND TUESDAY MORNING REACHING NEAR GALE FORCE IN THE NORTHWEST. WINDS WILL
VEERING WEST TO NORTHWESTERLY LATER TUESDAY AND DECREASE MODERATE TO FRESH
STILL STRONG IN THE NORTH AND IN THE EAST. WEATHER: BECOMING MOSTLY CLOUDY
WITH RAIN AND DRIZZLE SPREADING FROM THE WEST ON TUESDAY CLEARING TO MAINLY
FAIR WEATHER LATER BUT WITH SCATTERED SHOWERS IN NORTHERN PARTS.
